.TH LSC "1" "June 2026" "lsc 0.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lsc \- eza listing with an aligned comment column
.SH DESCRIPTION
Annotate files and directories with short comments that appear in a column
next to the names in an `eza` listing. With no action flag, lsc lists PATH (or
the current directory). Only a single directory argument is resolved for
comments; with multiple paths or globs, comments resolve against the current
directory. Any flag not listed below is passed through to eza, e.g.
`lsc \fB\-la\fR \fB\-\-color\fR=\fI\,never\/\fR`.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
lsc [OPTION]... [PATH]...
lsc \fB\-\-set\fR FILE TEXT
lsc \fB\-\-rm\fR FILE
lsc \fB\-\-get\fR FILE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-set\fR FILE TEXT
set FILE's manifest comment (empty TEXT removes it,
same as \fB\-\-rm\fR); `\-\-set . TEXT` captions the directory
.TP
\fB\-\-rm\fR FILE
remove FILE's manifest comment, if any
.TP
\fB\-\-get\fR FILE
print FILE's effective comment (inline or manifest)
.TP
\fB\-\-fetch\-icloud\fR, \fB\-\-fetch\fR
read evicted iCloud files too (forces an iCloud
download if needed; default skips them)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-hilite\-recent\fR, \fB\-\-no\-hilite\fR
do not highlight just\-changed comments (on by default)
.TP
\fB\-\-hilite\-recent\fR, \fB\-\-hilite\fR
force highlighting of just\-changed comments on
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
show version number and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
show this help and exit
.SS "Comments:"
.IP
Comments come from two sources, with an inline magic line taking precedence
over the manifest. The inline form is a `comment:` line near the top of a text
file, after a //, #, \fB\-\-\fR, or ; marker (case\-insensitive, optional indent). The
manifest form is a per\-directory .lsc\-comments.json file mapping each bare
filename to its comment text; it is plain JSON, so it syncs through iCloud and
travels with the directory (unlike xattrs, which iCloud sync may strip).
.IP
Both \fB\-\-set\fR and \fB\-\-rm\fR act on the manifest only; they warn (on stderr) but still
act when an in\-file magic line would shadow the manifest entry in a listing.
.IP
A manifest entry keyed "." is the directory's own caption (set with
`lsc \fB\-\-set\fR . "..."`); it prints left\-aligned as a header line above the
listing.
